<div id="review_252122376" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/252122376" />
    <a title="Ahmad Sharabiani" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/614778-ahmad-sharabiani"><img alt="Ahmad Sharabiani" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1194930432p2/614778.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/252122376?book_show_action=true">Dec 28, 2011</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Ahmad Sharabiani" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Ahmad Sharabiani" href="/user/show/614778-ahmad-sharabiani">Ahmad Sharabiani</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9789648944631" href="/book/show/13328650">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/614778-ahmad-sharabiani?shelf=fiction">fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/614778-ahmad-sharabiani?shelf=historical">historical</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/614778-ahmad-sharabiani?shelf=20th-century">20th-century</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/614778-ahmad-sharabiani?shelf=epic">epic</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer252122376" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13602234346177686070">The King Beyond the Gate (The Drenai Saga #2), David Gemmell<br/>The King Beyond The Gate is a fantasy novel by British writer David Gemmell. It was published in 1985. It was the second book published by Gemmell, after Legend, published a year earlier. The book is set in the same fictional world as Legend, that of the Drenai, but is not a sequel in the usual sense as the events of the two books take place around a century apart. Thus the main protagonists of Legend are long since dead and play little</span>
  <span id="freeText13602234346177686070" style="display:none">The King Beyond the Gate (The Drenai Saga #2), David Gemmell<br />The King Beyond The Gate is a fantasy novel by British writer David Gemmell. It was published in 1985. It was the second book published by Gemmell, after Legend, published a year earlier. The book is set in the same fictional world as Legend, that of the Drenai, but is not a sequel in the usual sense as the events of the two books take place around a century apart. Thus the main protagonists of Legend are long since dead and play little part in The King Beyond the Gate, other than passing mentions. This set a precedent for the entire Drenai series, in which very few characters appear in more than one novel, the gaps between novels sometimes running to centuries, giving a more epic, historical flavour to the series.<br />تاریخ نخستین خوانش: ماه دسامبر سال 2010 میلادی<br />عنوان: پادشاه آنسوی دروازه؛ نویسنده: دیوید گمل؛ مترجم: سهیلا فرزین نژاد؛ تهران، کتابسرای تندیس، 1389، در 471 ص؛ شابک: 9789648944631؛ موضوع: داستانهای نویسندگان انگلیسی قرن 20 م<br />داستانی گیرا و پر کشش است، در دنیای درنای میگذرد، اما ادامه اسطوره نیست، چند بار خوانده ام؛ بهتر است خود بخوانید. ا. شربیانی</span>
  <a data-text-id="13602234346177686070" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


